<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/0995001e439b479a54b2cac9b04992f8.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 5 and b = 7. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>8.6</li><li>35.5</li><li>54.5</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={5}^{{2}}+{7}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={25}+{49}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={74}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{74}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.6023252670426}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{8.6}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{5}}{{7}}\right)}}}\approx{35.537677791974}\approx{35.5}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{35.537677791974}^{\circ}\approx{54.462322208026}\approx{54.5}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>